# IMDB Reviews Word Cloud

This project generates a word cloud visualization from IMDB movie reviews.

## Project Structure

- `main.py`: Main script to load, clean, and visualize the IMDB reviews as a word cloud.
- `content/IMDB-Dataset.csv`: Dataset containing IMDB reviews and their sentiments.
- `wordcloud reviews.png`: Output image of the generated word cloud.
- `env/`: Python virtual environment (not included in version control).
- `.gitignore`: Ignores environment files and `.env`.

## Requirements

- Python 3.x
- pandas
- matplotlib
- wordcloud

## Setup

1. (Optional) Create and activate a virtual environment:

   ```sh
   python -m venv env
   source env/bin/activate  # On Windows: env\Scripts\activate
   ```

2. Install dependencies:

   ```sh
   pip install pandas matplotlib wordcloud
   ```

3. Ensure `content/IMDB-Dataset.csv` is present.

## Usage

Run the main script to generate and display the word cloud:

```sh
python main.py
```

A window will display the word cloud generated from the IMDB reviews.

## How it works

- Loads the IMDB dataset from [content/IMDB-Dataset.csv](content/IMDB-Dataset.csv).
- Cleans the review text (removes punctuation, lowercases, removes stopwords).
- Generates a word cloud image using the [`WordCloud`](https://github.com/amueller/word_cloud) library.
- Displays the word cloud using matplotlib.

